# Security & secrets

- Never print, log, echo, or commit secrets, API keys, exchange credentials, tokens,
  passwords, personal financial data, or audit records. Expose booleans, not values.
- Secrets come from environment / `Settings`; never hardcode literals. Real `.env*` files
  are gitignored; only `*.example` templates are committed.
- Sanitize and validate external inputs at boundaries. Apply least privilege. Fail closed.
- Do not enable real trading, billing charges, or external notification delivery by default.
- `render.yaml` and env examples must contain placeholders only.
